    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nProgress messages may be \"dangling\" i.e. they may never reach 100% progress. That leaves progress UIs (such as statusline or whatever else) with a difficult decision about whether they should drop/prune \"stale\" Progress messages: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/35428#discussion_r2298443894\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSimilar to how mappings optionally show the Lua origin with 'verbose' enabled (aka `nvim -V1`), Nvim can store debug info on a long-lived message (i.e. any message with an id).",
